# Vercel's Python builder prioritizes pyproject.toml over requirements.txt
# when both exist, and treats the project as a single-entrypoint app (needs
# ONE app.py/main.py/etc, or [tool.vercel] entrypoint) rather than
# auto-discovering each api/*.py as its own function — breaks our two-function
# (webhook + cron) setup. pyproject.toml/uv.lock are only needed for local uv
# tooling; hiding them from Vercel restores requirements.txt-based multi-
# function auto-discovery. See github.com/vercel/vercel/issues/14041.
pyproject.toml
uv.lock
.python-version
